# Changelog
All notable changes to the skin3d library will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.1.0] - 2025-12-31

**Major Release: Refactored Library with Enhanced Documentation**

### Added
- âœ¨ **Modular Architecture**: Refactored library structure with separated concerns
  - New `Render.ts` class replacing the previous `skin3d.ts` - Core rendering engine for 3D player models using Three.js
  - New modular structure with separate `index.ts` entry point for cleaner exports
  - Refactored module exports: `Model.ts`, `Render.ts`, `Animation.ts`, `Nametag.ts`

- ðŸ“š **Comprehensive Documentation Suite** (8 documentation files, 3,200+ lines)
  - GETTING_STARTED.md - Installation, setup, and framework integration (React, Vue, Svelte)
  - EXAMPLES.md - 10+ practical code examples
  - API_REFERENCE.md - Complete API documentation with all classes and methods
  - ARCHITECTURE.md - Library design, structure, and design patterns
  - ADVANCED_USAGE.md - Performance optimization, custom animations, and extensions
  - MIGRATION_GUIDE.md - Upgrade path from previous versions
  - TROUBLESHOOTING.md - Common issues and solutions
  - README.md - Documentation index and overview

- ðŸ§¹ **Dependency Cleanup**
  - Removed unused npm polyfills (path, url)
  - Optimized production bundle size
  - Improved tree-shaking with named exports

### Changed
- ðŸ”„ **Breaking Change:** Main class renamed from `View` to `Render`
  - Updated all imports and examples to use new name
  - Added migration guide for upgrading from v0.0.10

- ðŸ“¦ **Enhanced Module Structure**
  - Refactored library structure from monolithic entry point to modular component exports
  - Updated file naming convention (capitalized: `Animation.ts`, `Model.ts`, `Nametag.ts`, `Render.ts`)
  - Modified project dependencies in `package.json` to support new architecture

- ðŸ“– **Improved README**
  - Added recent changes section
  - Updated code examples with named imports
  - Added comprehensive documentation section
  - Added breaking changes notice with migration guide link

### Fixed
